### steps

1. npm install cypress as developer dependency
2. in package.json --> inside scripts --> "cypress":"cypress open"
3. npm start
4. npm run cypress
5. start E2E testing in chrome
6. select create an empty spec option
7. New spec
8. continue running the spec
9. create .eslintrc.json --> there is a chance that in cypress>e2e>spec.cy.js that it may throw an error that "cy" is not defined to nullify this error we have created .eslintrc.json

<!-- if it says cypress verification timed out  then  -> npx cypress verify -->

### Learning objectives

1. How to work with syncronous events,access elements and user events
